The paper deals with a geometric optimization problem involving planar points, which suggests that it could belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) category. The use of an exact algorithm and a sampling algorithm also suggests that it could belong to the algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) category. The problem involves finding a minimum enclosing parallelogram, which could also be relevant to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) category. The use of optimization techniques and the runtime analysis suggest that it could belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) category. Finally, the problem involves finding a geometric shape that covers a certain number of points, which could also be relevant to the graphics (cs.GC) category.
